<br>
In this instance, a very well-known guild Legacy of Steel was banned for a &quot;z axis&quot; exploit that has been readily indentified as a tactic that many, many guilds have used for a long while.<br>
<br>
I remember when a guild (can't remember the name but tigole posted about it in depth) was banned for &quot;exploiting&quot; in sleepers tomb.  Some members were banned and some suspended.  It caused a wildfire that spread through the majority of Everquest-related boards and many end game guild websites.  In fact, Gordon or Alan posted in depth about the issue on the EQ boards to clarify Verants side.  In that instance, the guild in question was used to make an example to other guilds that were also using the tactic.<br>
<br>
But, there is a major difference between using a tactic that allows you to aggro/harm a mob without the mob being able to harm you as opposed to a z axis warp that allows to fight the same mob in another area.  I would agree that if LoS was using this z axis tactic to enable them to kill this mini boss with some type of major advantage (i.e. clerics being able to CH the MT with the boss not being able to harm them) I would say that would merit suspensions.  But, it appears to me that all LoS did was show verant a bug that they need to fix.<br>
<br>
As usual, instead of verant just simply patching their bugs that they find based on END GAME GUILDS TESTING THEM WHILE STILL PAYING PER MONTH, they choose to suspend their value added testers at a poor attempt to set an example for other vex thal time sinked guilds and increase the average cock size of the GMs by 5%.<br>
<br>
At this point, verant needs to step in for their incompetant GMs (assuming this suspension was based on only a handful of GMs) and un-suspend LoS.  I would even say it reasonable to add the generic &quot;Do not do anything you feel is exploitation&quot; public service message.  Hell, an apology isn't even warranted, the statement they will make by unsuspending LoS will be enough for me.<br>
<br>
Well, please flame me but I am just speaking as honest as I can get.<br>
